description: Japanese companies Honda and Nissan plan to merge operations in response to tough business challenges, potentially affecting their global and Indian markets. The merger faces complexities in India due to independent production setups and Nissan's partnership with Renault. The future of Nissan and Renault's collaboration in Chennai remains uncertain.
title: India to be key challenge as Honda, Nissan talk merger
Fire breaks out at singer Shaan's residential building in Mumbai

description: BJP alleges Congress disrespected B R Ambedkar during his lifetime by ignoring his contributions and not awarding him with Bharat Ratna or Padma awards. BJP leader Ravi Shankar Prasad demands an apology, pointing out Congress' hypocrisy in remembering Ambedkar's legacy while criticizing past actions.
title: Congress always insulted Ambedkar, now claiming legacy, alleges BJP

description: A compliance audit of income tax collections from distilleries and breweries in several Indian states has revealed significant under-reporting of sales, resulting in estimated tax implications of Rs 12,800 crore over a 10-year period. The Comptroller and Auditor General found deficiencies in income tax assessment units and recommended systemic improvements to prevent such discrepancies in the future.
title: 11 distilleries cooked books, caused Rs 13,000 crore tax shortfall: CAG

description: Bastar’s administration found a man named ‘Sunny Leone’ fraudulently receiving Rs 1,000 monthly from Chhattisgarh’s Mahtari Vandan Yojana for women. His alleged accomplices were also identified and actions taken against them. The account was frozen, and recovery proceedings started. The discovery highlights flaws in the verification process of the scheme benefiting married women.
title: Bastar's ‘Sunny Leone’ caught drawing Rs 1k dole from govt; man held

description: Nasa announced that NISAR, the advanced earth observation satellite developed by India and the US, is set to launch in March 2025. With dual-frequency radar, NISAR will monitor planetary changes with precision, aiding in climate change understanding and disaster response. It will provide high-resolution images and track surface changes, benefiting global natural resource management.
title: World's most expensive Indo-US satellite likely to be launched in March: Nasa

description: WWE Royal Rumble 2025, set for February 1st, will break tradition by not being held in January. Top contenders to win this yearly spectacle include ex-champions like Drew McIntyre and Roman Reigns, CM Punk and veteran John Cena, who might aim for a record 17th WWE World Title in his last tenure.
title: 4 WWE Superstars who are favorite to win the 2025 Royal Rumble

description: Pharma department has reprimanded AbbVie Healthcare for sending 30 doctors to Paris and Monaco, spending over Rs 1.9 crore, violating uniform travel and hospitality guidelines. The National Medical Commission has been asked to investigate misconduct by doctors. AbbVie justified the expense as industry practice but the department suggested supporting underprivileged patients instead.
title: Pharma company hauled up for taking doctors on foreign trips

description: A claims tribunal in Meerut has ordered 69 individuals to pay over Rs 12 lakh for damaging public property during protests against the Agnipath scheme in 2022. The protests saw trains torched and buses damaged in Aligarh. The order was passed under the UP Recovery of Damages Act, 2020.
title: 2022 Agnipath protest: 69 people from Aligarh to pay Rs 12 lakh damages

description: A Joint Parliamentary Committee's first meeting on 'one nation, one election' is set for Jan 8, with an agenda to assess the implications of simultaneous Lok Sabha and state assembly elections. The Constitution and Union Territories Laws Amendment Bills face strong opposition, needing a two-thirds majority for constitutional amendments.
title: Parliament panel to hold first meet on one nation, one election on Jan 8

description: Union Home Minister Amit Shah emphasizes cooperation with friendly nations on intelligence to detect anti-India outfits. He highlights the importance of new strategies to counter emerging threats, including cyber and psychological warfare, and calls for the use of AI and blockchain to address these security challenges.
title: Amit Shah eyes intel synergy with 'friendly' nations
Beef shops across Goa shut down after clash with cow vigilantes

description: The film fraternity mourned the passing of Shyam Benegal, a pioneer of New Wave cinema, who mentored numerous actors and revolutionized Indian cinema with films like 'Ankur' and 'Manthan'. His work, celebrated for its raw and real storytelling, leaves a lasting legacy.
title: 'Benegal told raw & real stories about ordinary people'
Denied cabinet berth, Bhujbal meets Maharashtra CM Fadnavis
ED seizes flat in name of Dawood brother’s aide

description: Pramathes Ghosal, a private tutor from Bengal's Hooghly district, was sentenced to death for the brutal triple murder of his elderly parents and married sister in November 2021. He claimed financial pressure led to the crime, but locals disputed his assertion, stating he earned enough.
title: Saved after suicide bid, man gets death sentence for killing 3 of his family
We gave jobs to 10 lakh youth in 18 months: PM Modi

description: India faces diplomatic pressure after Bangladesh's interim government requested the extradition of ousted PM Sheikh Hasina, accused of 'crimes against humanity.' The Indian foreign ministry has yet to respond formally, weighing legal commitments and geopolitical considerations, as extradition under the 2013 treaty could complicate relations with their long-time ally.
title: Extradite Sheikh Hasina for trial, Bangladesh writes to India

description: History appears to be overlooked at St Francis Church in Fort Kochi, with no events marking 500 years since Vasco da Gama's death. Post-colonial perspectives often view da Gama negatively, conflicting with older views of his contributions to global trade and cultural exchange.
title: 500 years on, Vasco da Gama hailed in Lisbon, ignored in Kochi

description: Travis Hunter deactivates his Instagram to support fiancée Leanna Lenee amid backlash from a three-year-old video of her dancing inappropriately with another man. The resurfacing of this video has led to severe online trolling and criticism. Kelce expressed his exhaustion with the negativity, and Lenee made her social media accounts private to escape further scrutiny.
title: Travis Hunter deletes Insta in defense of fiancée after old video goes viral

description: Pakistan plans to acquire 40 J-35 stealth fighters from China, marking the first export of Beijing’s fifth-generation jets to a foreign ally. The J-35A will publicly debut after the PLAAF anniversary. This move is expected to shift the military balance between Pakistan and India.
title: Pakistan plans to purchase 40 Chinese J-35 stealth fighter jets

description: In the early 1970s, Pakistan attempted to replicate India's Cirus reactor design, which was integral to India's first nuclear test in 1974. Munir Ahmed Khan led the effort, but challenges arose from differences between the Cirus reactor and Pakistan's Kanupp. Recently, the US imposed sanctions on Pakistan for its advanced missile technology.
title: How Pakistan ‘copied’ design of India’s 1960 Cirus reactor

description: Khalistan Zindabad Force (KZF), a radical Sikh group established in 1993 by Ranjeet Singh Neeta, aims to create a sovereign Khalistan state. With strong ties to Pakistan's ISI, KZF targets police facilities in Punjab and radicalizes Sikhs globally. Neeta was declared a terrorist under UAPA in 2020.
title: Khalistan Zindabad Force chief hails from J&K, is now in Pakistan
Farmers' protest: Dallewal, 28 days into fast, may not recover fully, say docs

description: ​"He (Luigi Mangione)  was on display for everyone to see in the biggest staged perp walk I've ever seen in my career. It was absolutely unnecessary. He's been cooperative with law enforcement, he's been in custody for over a week; he waived extradition..."lawyer Karen Friedman Agnifilo said as Mangione appeared in the court today and pleaded not guilty to the state charge.
title: Luigi Mangione is a young man, not human ping-pong ball: What his lawyer said in the court
21 held for defrauding 16,000 people of Rs 125 cr in massive cyber fraud

description: Telangana police summoned actor Allu Arjun after a stampede at a 'Pushpa 2' premiere in Hyderabad caused a woman's death and injured her son. The actor was released on bail, and the family received Rs 50 lakh in financial aid. Protests ensued at Arjun's residence, demanding further compensation, leading to increased security.
title: Allu Arjun summoned by police for questioning in stampede case

description: R Ashwin, 38, recently retired from international cricket citing a lack of creative satisfaction. He plans to continue club cricket, including the IPL. Ashwin expressed gratitude for the game and overwhelming support post-retirement, including calls from legends like Sachin Tendulkar and Kapil Dev. The cricketer visualizes more creativity in his future endeavors.
title: Ashwin clears the air about popular misconception

description: Elon Musk's multifaceted role as a tech visionary, social media influencer, and political force is reshaping industries and politics. From revolutionizing electric vehicles and space travel to his controversial acquisition of Twitter, Musk's influence spans beyond technology into global political dynamics, drawing comparisons to George Soros and raising ethical questions about billionaire-led activism.
title: US Republicans embrace 'Prime Minister' Elon Musk

description: The re-entry of a Chinese satellite created a fireball display over the southern United States on Sunday night. The SuperView-1 02 satellite burned up over New Orleans, causing sightings across several states. This event drew both awe and concern from the public regarding falling space debris.
title: Watch: 'Fireballs' light up US sky as Chinese satellite burns up in atmosphere

description: US President-elect Donald Trump appoints Chennai-born Sriram Krishnan as White House advisor on AI policy, sparking debates among MAGA radicals. Krishnan's tech background includes roles at Microsoft, Twitter, Yahoo!, and Facebook. His views on H-1B visas and skilled immigration raise concerns among nativist groups.
title: Trump appoints Sriram Krishnan as AI czar; backlash from MAGA

description: Becky Lynch, former WWE Women's Champion, is rumored to return as WWE transitions to Netflix. Key moments in her career include her 'The Man' gimmick in 2018, iconic bloody nose incident, winning two titles at WrestleMania 2019, a triumphant SummerSlam return in 2021, and her intense rivalry with Charlotte Flair at Survivor Series 2021.
title: 5 Illustrious moments to remember this holiday

description: Jagadguru Swami Rambhadracharya criticized RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat’s remark on not raking up Ram temple-like issues elsewhere, calling it influenced by appeasement politics. He expressed displeasure at the silence on violence in Sambhal and atrocities against Hindus. Bhagwat emphasized harmony among faiths and avoiding extremism in a lecture on 'Vishwaguru Bharat'.
title: Seer, who played key role in Ram Mandir case, lashes out at RSS chief

description: The Dalai Lama, 89, reassures followers about his health, predicting a lifespan of 110 years. Despite recent knee surgery, his recovery is progressing. Living in exile since 1959, he advocates for Tibetan autonomy. Amidst concerns over his succession, the spiritual leader's stance challenges China's influence on Tibetan Buddhism's future.
title: 'I may live 110 years': Dalai Lama amid health concerns
After Kejriwal's Delhi snub, Congress stares at RJD challenge in Bihar

description: Veteran filmmaker Shyam Benegal passed away at the age of 90 due to chronic kidney disease. Known for classics such as Ankur and Nishant, he left an indelible mark on Indian parallel cinema. Tributes poured in from political leaders nationwide, honoring his contributions and influence in the film industry.
title: 'Loss for humanity': Rahul, Mamata pay tribute to filmmaker Shyam Benegal

description: The 'Pushpa-2' production team provided Rs 50 lakhs to the family of a woman who died in a stampede during the film's screening in Hyderabad. Producer Naveen Yerneni visited the woman's injured son in the hospital. Allu Arjun announced a Rs 25 lakhs donation and issued a public apology following criticism over the incident.
title: Pushpa 2 producers give Rs 50 lakhs to stampede victim's family

description: President Biden commuted the sentences of 37 federal death row inmates, sparing them from execution, but excluded three men convicted of notorious mass killings: Robert Bowers, who killed 11 worshippers at Pittsburgh's Tree of Life Synagogue in 2018; Dylann Roof, a white supremacist who murdered nine Black churchgoers in Charleston, South Carolina, in 2015; and Dzhokhar Tsarnaev, who carried out the 2013 Boston Marathon bombing, killing three and injuring hundreds. Biden, opposed to the death penalty, justified his decision by citing the heinous nature of these hate-driven and terroristic acts. The three men remain on death row under federal sentencing.
title: The three men even Joe Biden couldn't pardon

description: Blinkit, owned by Zomato, is offering free Christmas cakes for orders above Rs 499 if a tweet gets 5,000 likes. Highlighting the festive promotion on social media, the quick commerce platform invites users to like their post to claim the offer.
title: Blinkit to offer free Christmas cake on select orders if ….

description: India's premier off-spinner R Ashwin announced his retirement from Test cricket, leaving the game with 537 wickets in 106 matches, only behind Anil Kumble in India's history. Despite feeling he had more to offer, Ashwin decided to retire mid-series against Australia. Ashwin, with an engineering background, also had a notable career in ODIs and T20Is for India.
title: 'Don't cry because its over': Heartfelt sentiments from R Ashwin

description: Google CEO Sundar Pichai introduces a revised definition of 'Googleyness,' condensing it into six principles to offer clearer guidance for employees. The redefined framework addresses previous criticisms of fostering workplace homogeneity and aligns with Google's updated hiring guidelines focusing on diversity and inclusion since 2019.
title: Google CEO Sundar Pichai to employees: The definition of 'Googleyness' needs …

description: Unidentified individuals vandalized Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar's statue in Ahmedabad, damaging the nose and spectacles, leading to local protests. Authorities filed a case under several sections of the Bharatiya Nyay Sanhita. This incident follows another act of vandalism in Parbhani, Maharashtra, which sparked violent protests. Locals demand swift action against those responsible for these attacks.
title: BR Ambedkar's statue vandalised in Ahmedabad, sparks protests

description: A cargo ship at Istanbul port capsized due to imbalanced cargo loading, leading to a rescue operation for the crew. Ten crew members were rescued quickly, while five others escaped by jumping into the water. One crew member was slightly injured and taken to a hospital.
title: Watch: Cargo ship rolls onto its side at Istanbul Port

description: Congress leader Rahul Gandhi visited the family of Somnath Suryawanshi, a Dalit law student who died in custody following protests in Parbhani, Maharashtra.  Gandhi alleged Suryawanshi was murdered for protecting the Constitution and blamed the RSS ideology.  Chief minister Fadnavis called Gandhi's visit a political move to incite caste hatred and announced a judicial inquiry into the death and protests.
title: 'Attempt to create hatred': BJP on Rahul meeting Parbhani victim's kin

description: Jacob Bethell, hailed as a 'generational talent' by R Ashwin, is Rugby School’s shining star. The Barbados-born cricketer, now destined for Royal Challengers Bengaluru, made remarkable strides by debuting in ODI, T20I, and Test cricket within three months, showcasing his seamless transition from a classy Test batter to a potent white-ball cricketer.
title: Father played with Root’s dad, son to partner Virat Kohli

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi expressed his sorrow over efforts to disrupt peace, referencing the recent attack at a German Christmas market. Attending a Christmas event, he emphasized love and unity as taught by Lord Christ. Modi also highlighted India's humanitarian responses during major crises, stressing a commitment to global aid and human rights.
title: 'It pains my heart': PM Modi on 'attempts to spread violence' in society

description: Israeli intelligence agents revealed a decade-long operation involving booby-trapped pagers and walkie-talkies supplied to Hezbollah.  Detonated in September 2024, the devices killed approximately 30 militants and wounded many more, creating widespread fear and demonstrating Israel's reach. The operation unfolded amidst escalating conflict between Israel and Hezbollah following the Hamas attack in October 2023.
title: 'Pretend world of Mossad': How Israel weaponized devices in plot against Hezbollah

description: Zara Dar, a former YouTuber who once preached the gospel of machine learning and neural networks to over 100,000 subscribers, has swapped her lab coat for something, well, a little spicier. She dropped out of her PhD program to become an OnlyFans content creator, and folks, the gamble has paid off. In just a short time, she's raked in a cool $1 million—a number most professors can only dream of seeing on their grant proposals.
title: Zara Dar: How a PhD dropout and OnlyFans creator made million dollars

description: A senior TuM member, Javed Munshi, was arrested by West Bengal STF and Jammu and Kashmir Police in South 24 Parganas. Munshi, acting under LeT instructions, planned to escape to Pakistan via Bangladesh. He was found disguising as a shawl seller with ties to other terror outfits.
title: 'Escape strategy': Terrorist nabbed in Bengal was trying to reach Pak via B'desh

description: The future of James Bond films is uncertain due to disagreements between the Broccoli family and Amazon.  Barbara Broccoli, inheriting control of the franchise, distrusts Amazon's approach to filmmaking, stalling development.
title: James Bond has dodged over 4,000 bullets; still can’t ‘beat’ this one from Amazon

description: Several states in India have declared winter vacations for schools, providing students a break during the cold season. Delhi schools will observe holidays from January 1-15, 2025, while Uttar Pradesh is expected to close from December 25 to January 5, 2025. Punjab has announced a winter break from December 24-31, 2024, and other states like Haryana, Jammu and Kashmir, Rajasthan, and Bihar have also set varying vacation schedules. These holidays offer students a welcome respite during winter.
title: Winter break for schools in Delhi, UP & other states: Check details
'Absolute necessity': Why Trump wants to buy Greenland

description: The parliamentary panel's first meeting on 'One Nation, One Election' will occur on January 8, with the panel now comprising 39 members to ensure broad representation. Law minister Arjun Ram Meghwal introduced the resolutions, and the committee is to submit its report by the first day of the last week of the next session.
title: First JPC meeting for 'ONOE' bills to be held on January 8

description: A Saudi-born psychiatrist drove an SUV into a German Christmas market, killing five and injuring over 200.  Saudi Arabia had warned Germany about the suspect's extremist views multiple times, but German authorities failed to act. The attack has sparked outrage and raised questions about Germany's security protocols and the handling of intelligence warnings.
title: 'Migration kills': 'Islamisation of Europe' behind German car attack?

description: Veteran filmmaker Shyam Benegal, who ushered in parallel cinema in India, passed away at 90. Known for his realism and depth, his acclaimed works include Ankur, Nishant, and Zubeidaa. Honored with Padma Shri and Padma Bhushan, Benegal's contributions to Indian cinema remain unparalleled. His death signifies the end of a pioneering era in filmmaking.
title: Shyam Benegal, revered filmmaker with 18 national awards, dies at 90

description: Ranveer Singh and Deepika Padukone have requested photographers to respect their daughter Dua's privacy. Celebrating her arrival, Ranveer invited a few photographers to his clubhouse, expressing joy over having "Laxmi" in their home. The couple welcomed Dua on September 8, 2024, sharing her name during Diwali celebrations.
title: Ranveer and Deepika invite paparazzi, request privacy for daughter Dua

description: Anupam Mittal satirizes the 18% GST on caramelized popcorn, highlighting the different tax rates compared to salted popcorn (12%).  His post on X (formerly Twitter) sparked online debate, with users humorously suggesting smuggling sugar into theaters to avoid the higher tax.
title: Anupam Mittal takes a jibe at GST on popcorns: Man arrested at theatre for...
Adani spreads wings in aviation, to acquire leading MRO Air Works

description: The Indian Embassy in Germany is in close contact with the seven Indian nationals injured in a car attack at the Magdeburg Christmas Market. Three have been discharged, while four remain under treatment. The attack by a Saudi psychiatrist killed five and injured over 200, leading to enhanced security and market cancellations in Germany.
title: 7 Indians injured in Germany attack; embassy says in 'close contact'

description: The central government's new GST rates on popcorn—5% for salted, 12% for branded, and 18% for caramel—have sparked widespread criticism.  Former economic advisers slammed the decision's complexity and minimal revenue gain, while opposition leaders called it absurd.  The finance minister defended the caramel popcorn tax, citing its sugar content, but public sentiment remains largely negative.
title: New GST rates on popcorn spark backlash on social media

description: A group claiming affiliation with the OU-JAC vandalized actor Allu Arjun's Hyderabad residence, protesting a stampede death at a 'Pushpa 2' screening.  Six individuals were arrested and granted bail.  Political tensions flared as opposition parties criticized the ruling Congress over law and order, while Allu Arjun's family urged calm and reliance on legal processes.
title: BRS vs Congress intensifies over Allu Arjun house vandalisation; all 6 accused get bail
Trump's choice of Indian-origin Sriram Krishnan as AI advisor sparks outrage

description: Burt, the iconic saltwater crocodile from 'Crocodile Dundee', died in Darwin at age 90. Known for his fiery temperament and impressive size, he lived at Crocosaurus Cove since 2008. His caretakers honored him as a "force of nature," and the park plans to install a commemorative sign in his memory.
title: Burt, iconic saltwater crocodile from 'Crocodile Dundee', passes away

description: A woman drank four liters of water for detoxification. She experienced headache, nausea, and confusion. She then had a seizure and lost consciousness. Doctors diagnosed her with hyponatremia.  Her sodium levels were dangerously low.  She received treatment in the ICU for three days.  She recovered and was discharged.  Doctors recommend two to three liters of water daily.
title: How overdrinking water for detoxification almost killed a woman
Trump wants to buy Greenland, calls US control 'vital' after Panama Canal push

description: Krunal Pandya, Baroda captain and Royal Challengers Bangalore's newest recruit, showcased his resurgent form with a blistering 80-run knock and a controlled bowling performance in the Vijay Hazare Trophy. RCB secured Pandya for Rs 5.75 crore after a bidding war with Rajasthan Royals.
title: 148 strike rate and 3 sixes! RCB’s new recruit Krunal returns to form

description: The Department of Telecommunications (DoT) has directed telecom providers to play cybercrime awareness messages as caller tunes 8-10 times daily for three months.  This initiative aims to combat rising cyber fraud. The caller tunes, provided by the Indian Cybercrime Coordination Centre, warn against scams like impersonation by officials.  This follows government action to block fraudulent SIM cards and devices.
title: ‘Saavdhaan Agar Aapko Anjane …’: DoT’s ‘warning message' to Jio, Airtel & Voda

description: Mumbai all-rounder Tanush Kotian is on standby to join India's Test squad in Melbourne as a potential replacement for Ravichandran Ashwin. The 26-year-old off-spinner recently impressed during India A's tour of Australia and shone in the Ranji Trophy, leading Mumbai to victory. While awaiting official confirmation, Kotian's first-class record boasts over 2500 runs and 100 wickets, highlighting his all-round capabilities.
title: Who is Tanush Kotian? R Ashwin's replacement for Ind vs Aus series

description: Luigi Mangione will be arraigned Monday for the murder of UnitedHealth Group CEO Brian Thompson. Mangione faces state murder charges, including terrorism-related counts. He also faces federal charges for stalking and killing Thompson. A notebook with writings against health insurance companies was found. Some view Mangione as a symbol against high healthcare costs.
title: Luigi Mangione faces terror charges in UnitedHealth CEO murder case

description: TL;DR: New Jersey thought it had a drone problem. Turns out, it just has a lot of planes. Maybe next time, folks, use those flight apps before declaring the arrival of aliens.
title: Were New Jersey drone sightings UFOs or aliens? The actual truth is...

description: India's star pacer Mohammed Shami is not fully fit for the remaining two Tests of Border-Gavaskar Trophy against Australia, owing to minor swelling on his left knee, the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) confirmed on Monday. Following an evaluation by the BCCI medical team, it has been established that additional time is necessary to manage the controlled bowling workload on his knee. As a result, he has been declared unfit for selection in the final two Tests of the Border-Gavaskar Trophy.
title: Shami not fit for remaining two Tests of BGT

description: Former Supreme Court judge V Ramasubramanian was appointed chairperson of the National Human Rights Commission of India (NHRC).  The position was vacant since June. Ramasubramanian served on the Supreme Court from 2019 to 2023 and was Chief Justice of Himachal Pradesh high court.  A high-powered committee including PM Modi selected him.
title: Ex-Supreme Court judge V Ramasubramanian appointed NHRC chief

description: Indian External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar will visit the United States from December 24-29, marking the first high-level diplomatic interaction since Donald Trump's presidential win. During his six-day trip, Jaishankar will meet with US counterparts to address bilateral, regional, and global matters and convene with Indian Consul Generals across the US.
title: Jaishankar to begin 6-day visit to US from December 24

description: A stampede at the Hyderabad premiere of Allu Arjun's 'Pushpa 2' tragically killed a woman and critically injured her son.  Police, who had warned the theatre about crowd control, were unaware of Arjun's presence.  The police commissioner's controversial remarks about national media sparked outrage and a subsequent apology. Protests erupted at Arjun's home, leading to arrests and increased security.
title: CV Anand apologises for his remarks over Allu Arjun stampede controversy

description: A Mangaluru resident fell victim to a WhatsApp APK scam, losing Rs 6.6 lakh. He received a message in a cricket group, deceptively renamed "Canara Bank," urging him to update KYC details via a link.
title: How a man lost Rs 6.6 lakh to 'Canara Bank KYC link’ sent on WhatsApp

description: NASA's Parker Solar Probe is scheduled for its closest-ever solar flyby on December 24, 2024, passing within 3.8 million miles of the Sun's surface. Traveling at 430,000 mph, the probe will gather data from the corona to understand its extreme heat, aiming to solve the mystery of why it's hotter than the Sun's surface.
title: Nasa’s Parker Solar Probe to make history on Christmas eve

description: Former Indian cricketer Vinod Kambli was hospitalised Saturday night following a decline in health. The 52-year-old's condition, though stable, remains critical. This follows a recent public appearance where his health struggles became apparent, prompting support offers from the 1983 World Cup-winning team, conditional on Kambli entering rehab.
title: Vinod Kambli admitted to Thane hospital in critical condition

description: Dar initially gained recognition for her educational YouTube channel, where she simplified complex scientific concepts and shared insights into subjects such as neural networks, gradient descent algorithms, and probability. Her engaging teaching style and ability to make STEM topics accessible to a wider audience garnered her a devoted following among students and science enthusiasts alike.
title: Meet Zara Dar who gave up academia to become an OnlyFans model

description: Indian Railways is set to launch two new train services for enhanced Kashmir connectivity. A centrally heated sleeper train will connect New Delhi and Srinagar, offering a 13-hour premium journey.
title: Indian Railways plans 2 special trains for Kashmir

description: India's wicketkeeper-batter Dhruv Jurel won a cash prize of $300 for his exceptional performance in a fielding drill.  The drill, designed to sharpen fielding skills and boost team energy in preparation for the Boxing Day Test against Australia, involved players hitting targets for points.  With the series tied 1-1, Team India aims to take the lead in Melbourne.
title: Watch: Jurel wins cash reward in India's fielding drill

description: Cheteshwar Pujara advises young opener Yashasvi Jaiswal to temper his aggression and show more patience at the crease. Jaiswal's recent struggles follow a stellar 161-run knock, prompting Pujara to suggest emulating KL Rahul's approach of capitalizing on fuller deliveries. Pujara believes Jaiswal is rushing his shots and should focus on solid defense, especially against Mitchell Starc, to earn scoring opportunities.
title: 'Even Sehwag was aggressive': Pujara slams Jaiswal

description: Indian chess star Tania Sachdev publicly expressed her disappointment over the Delhi government's lack of recognition for her chess achievements. Despite winning medals at the Chess Olympiad and holding national and Commonwealth titles, Sachdev claims lack of acknowledgment from the state government.
title: Sachdev slams Delhi govt for lack of recognition; CM responds

description: Singer Rahul Vaidya revealed he has been blocked by Virat Kohli on Instagram, expressing confusion over the situation. Vaidya stated, "Aaj tak samajh mein nahi aaya, bhai ne block kyun kiya." Meanwhile, Kohli and Anushka Sharma recently celebrated their seventh anniversary and are reportedly planning to move to London.
title: Rahul Vaidya reacts to being blocked by Virat Kohli on Instagram

description: The Border-Gavaskar Trophy is level at 1-1 as India and Australia head into the crucial Boxing Day Test at the MCG. India aims to repeat their 2020 victory at this venue, while Australia hopes to regain their historical dominance. Bumrah is nearing 200 Test wickets, and Smith is on the cusp of 10,000 Test runs.
title: India vs Australia Boxing Day Test: Everything you should know

description: Russia denied reports of Asma al-Assad, wife of ousted Syrian President Bashar al-Assad, seeking a divorce and planning to leave Russia for the UK.  The Kremlin also dismissed claims of restrictions on Assad's movements, frozen assets, and the family receiving asylum in Russia after the fall of Damascus to rebel forces.
title: Russia reacts to reports of ousted Syrian President wife seeking divorce

description: Zoho founder Sridhar Vembu revealed he tried to recruit Sriram Krishnan in 2004 after being impressed by Krishnan's blog.  Microsoft, however, had already hired him. Krishnan was recently appointed as a senior AI policy advisor to the White House by Donald Trump.
title: When Zoho founder Sridhar Vembu lost chance to hire Donald Trump's AI advisor

description: BJP leader Ravi Shankar Prasad accused the Congress party of hypocrisy, citing their historical treatment of B.R. Ambedkar.  Prasad highlighted Congress's failure to support Ambedkar's memorial and questioned their silence on his resignation. He contrasted this with the BJP's efforts to honor Ambedkar, including building a memorial and demanding an apology from Congress for their past actions.
title: 'They forced him to resign': BJP hits back at Congress over Ambedkar row

description: A 150-year-old stepwell with marble flooring and four chambers was unearthed in Sambhal, Uttar Pradesh, during an excavation.  The discovery coincided with the reopening of a nearby temple.  Akhilesh Yadav commented on the find, criticizing the BJP-led government.  The ASI also surveyed a Kalki Vishnu temple and surrounding areas, promising a forthcoming report.
title: 'Will end up digging their own govt': Akhilesh slams BJP over Sambhal excavation

description: Star shooter Manu Bhaker's omission from the Khel Ratna award nominations has sparked surprise. Neither Bhaker nor the NRAI applied for the prestigious award, reportedly aiming for the Padma Shri instead. While Bhaker secured two historic bronze medals at the Paris Olympics, the federation's inaction on her Khel Ratna application raises questions.
title: The puzzle around Manu Bhaker's name missing from Khel Ratna list

description: Rishabh Pant charmed a young fan at the MCG, creating a heartwarming moment that went viral. The Border-Gavaskar Trophy is currently tied 1-1, with India's win in Perth and Australia's victory in Adelaide. India faces a challenge with their fragile top order as they head into the Boxing Day Test.
title: Pant's sweet conversation with a young fan goes viral. Watch

description: Congress leader Rahul Gandhi met the family of Somnath Suryavanshi, a Dalit man who died in judicial custody following violence in Parbhani, Maharashtra.  Gandhi alleged Suryavanshi was murdered because of his caste and for defending the Constitution,  contradicting official claims.  The incident stemmed from vandalism of a replica of the Constitution, leading to riots and Suryavanshi's arrest.
title: 'Killed because he was Dalit': Rahul visits kin of man who died in custody

description: Bangladesh formally asked India to return ousted Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina.  The interim government wants Hasina to face trial.  She is accused of mass killings during student protests.  An extradition treaty exists between the two nations. Hasina fled to India after protests ended her 15-year rule.  The government plans to use the treaty to bring her back.
title: Bangladesh sends India formal note seeking extradition of Sheikh Hasina

description: YouTube star Gaurav Taneja, aka "Flying Beast," pitched his health brand, Beast Life, on Shark Tank India Season 4. Vineeta Singh questioned his motivation, given his substantial social media earnings. Taneja's brand offers protein powders and other supplements. His appearance, teased in a promo clip, has generated excitement among his millions of followers.
title: Shark Tank India 4: YouTuber Gaurav Taneja to pitch his health brand

description: Simon Katich advises Australian batsmen to prioritize strike rotation and solid defense against Jasprit Bumrah's accurate bowling.  He cautions against reckless aggression, citing Australia's second-innings collapse in Brisbane.  Katich also suggests replacing the injury-prone Mitchell Marsh with Beau Webster for the Boxing Day Test.
title: Katich advises Aussie batters against over aggression vs Bumrah

description: Cheteshwar Pujara voiced concerns over India's bowling attack ahead of the Boxing Day Test, questioning its ability to take 20 wickets.  He highlighted the struggles of bowlers besides Bumrah and Siraj, and the lack of a strong supporting bowling unit.  Pujara also praised Mitchell Starc's improved performance, emphasizing the need for Indian batsmen to navigate his potent opening spells effectively.
title: 'Indian bowling looking a little weak': Pujara

description: Bharat Global falsely claimed to have won large orders from corporates such as Reliance Industries Ltd., Tata Group, McCain India Agro Pvt. and UPL Ltd., the Securities and Exchange Board of India said in an initial order.
title: Why this stock’s 10,000% rally is under scrutiny

description: Seven Australian cricketers shared their one-word impressions of the ICC, BCCI, and Indian cricket.  Several players described the BCCI as "powerful" or "rulers," while the ICC was labeled as "boss" or "leaders."  Indian cricket was characterized as "strong" and "talented."  These insights come ahead of the fourth Test between India and Australia.
title: ICC, BCCI and Indian cricket in one word? Australian cricketers answer

description: Delhi High Court denied anticipatory bail to ex-IAS probationer Puja Khedkar, accused of fraudulently using OBC and disability quotas in the 2022 UPSC exam. Justice Chandra Dhari Singh cited a strong case against her, emphasizing the need to investigate the alleged conspiracy. The UPSC and Delhi Police opposed Khedkar's plea, accusing her of misrepresentation and seeking further attempts.
title: UPSC cheating case: Ex-trainee IAS Puja Khedkar denied anticipatory bail

description: Popular music composer duo Sachet and Parampara Tandon recently welcomed their first child, a baby boy. The joyous couple shared the news via a heartwarming social media video, showcasing tender moments with their newborn. The video features the couple holding their baby's tiny feet and hands, concluding with a shot of teddy bears and a baby doll.
title: Musician couple Sachet and Parampara blessed with a baby boy

description: PV Sindhu wed Venkata Datta Sai in a grand Udaipur ceremony.  Union Minister Gajendra Singh Shekhawat shared a captivating photo of the couple, offering his blessings.  Pre-wedding festivities included sangeet, haldi, and mehendi ceremonies. The families, longtime acquaintances, planned the wedding swiftly to accommodate Sindhu's training schedule.
title: PV Sindhu marries Venkata Datta, look at first pic

description: Stock market holidays 2025: Indian stock exchanges, BSE and NSE, have announced 14 trading holidays for 2025.  These include festivals like Holi, Diwali, and Christmas, along with observances such as Maharashtra Day and Mahatma Gandhi Jayanti. Check the full stock market holidays list for 2025 here:
title: Stock market holidays 2025: Check full list

description: Delhi BJP released a charge sheet against AAP government.  BJP criticized AAP's handling of pollution and alleged scams.  Kejriwal defended his government's work.  He highlighted improvements in electricity, water, and other areas.  Kejriwal also launched new schemes for women. BJP labeled these schemes as election promises.  Delhi Assembly elections are scheduled for February.
title: Delhi polls: BJP releases 'Aarop Patra' against AAP govt; Kejriwal reacts

description: A Chhattisgarh man, Virendra Joshi, fraudulently opened a bank account under actress Sunny Leone's name, listing Johnny Sins as her husband, to exploit the Mahtari Vandan Yojana. He withdrew ₹10,000 before authorities froze the account and filed an FIR.  An investigation is underway to determine how the application was approved, and the withdrawn amount will be recovered.
title: 'Sunny Leone, wife of Johnny Sins': How man dodged govt to get Rs 1,000

description: Mohandas Pai criticizes India's corporate sector for widening wage disparity.  Executive salaries have surged while fresher salaries stagnated at a mere 15% increase over 13 years. Pai calls for fairer compensation, especially for entry-level and contract workers, citing continued profitability despite automation.
title: Infosys' ex-CFO calls out ‘biggest’ salary disparity in IT companies in India

description: The central government has amended the Right to Education (RTE) Rules, 2010, allowing states to conduct regular examinations for students in Classes 5 and 8, with the option to hold them back if they fail. This change comes five years after the 2019 amendment to the RTE Act, which scrapped the “no-detention” policy. While some states have embraced the new system, others, like Kerala, remain opposed, citing concerns over added pressure on students.
title: Centre amends RTE rules, states can now fail students in classes 5 and 8

description: Infosys co-founder Narayana Murthy reiterated his support for a 70-hour workweek, emphasizing productivity over work-life balance.  Congress MP Karti Chidambaram countered, advocating for a four-day workweek and prioritizing efficiency and social harmony.  The debate highlights differing perspectives on work culture and India's economic progress.
title: Karti Chidambaram's take on Narayana Murthy 70-hour workweek stance

description: Abdullah Shafique etched an unwanted record, becoming the first batsman with ducks in all matches of a three-ODI series. His three ducks against South Africa pushed his 2024 total to seven in 21 innings, surpassing previous Pakistani records. Pakistan registered a 3-0 series victory against South Africa, securing the third ODI by 36 runs via the DLS method.
title: Pak opener fails to score a single run in entire series

description: Asma al-Assad, wife of ousted Syrian president Bashar al-Assad, has reportedly filed for divorce in a Russian court. She seeks to relocate to London after expressing discontent with life in Moscow. Holding dual British-Syrian citizenship, Asma spent her youth in London and married Assad in 2000.
title: 'Ousted Syrian President Assad’s wife files for divorce, unhappy in Moscow'

description: Two BJP MPs, injured during a scuffle with Congress leaders at the new Parliament building, were discharged from the hospital Friday. The confrontation arose from a BJP protest against alleged disrespect towards Dr. B.R. Ambedkar. During the incident, MP Pratap Sarangi suffered a head injury, and MP Mukesh Rajput briefly lost consciousness.
title: Sansad scuffle: Injured BJP MPs Sarangi and Rajput discharged from hospital

description: Hyderabad Police Commissioner CV Anand issued a stern warning to bouncers following a stampede at Sandhya Theatre during actor Allu Arjun's film premiere. Anand held VIPs responsible for their bouncers' actions and refused to comment on allegations against Arjun's team silencing the victim's family. Police recounted the chaotic events, alleging Arjun delayed his exit despite being informed of the fatality.
title: Pushpa 2 stampede case: What happened on December 4, according to cops

description: Varun Dhawan's 'Baby John' is set for a Christmas release, facing box office competition from 'Pushpa 2' and 'Mufasa'. Advance bookings suggest a decent opening, but the film's success hinges on sustaining momentum amidst strong rivals.  The Hindi remake of 'Theri' features Keerthy Suresh and boasts action sequences choreographed by international experts.
title: 'Baby John' advance booking Day 1: Varun Dhawan starrer collects Rs 50 Lakh

description: Nineteen-year-old Australian cricketer Sam Konstas is poised for a potential Test debut against India on Boxing Day. He's been studying Jasprit Bumrah's bowling and even gleaned insights from KL Rahul. Konstas's impressive recent form, including a century against India in a warm-up match, has earned him praise. Konstas, who smashed 14 fours and a six in his brilliant knock against India in the warm-up match, where he was named Man of the Match, draws inspiration from former Australia allrounder Shane Watson.
title: 'Watched Jasprit Bumrah, spoke to KL Rahul'

description: India and Japan are finalizing designs for bullet trains on the Mumbai-Ahmedabad corridor, modifying Shinkansen trains for Indian conditions.  These modifications include enhanced luggage capacity, higher temperature tolerance, and dust resistance.
title: Japan trains to be tweaked for India’s first bullet train project - details

description: Cricketer Aakash Chopra has revealed his top five T20I batsmen of 2024. India's Rohit Sharma tops the list, lauded for his consistency and aggressive captaincy during the World Cup. England's Phil Salt and Jos Buttler secure second and fifth place respectively, showcasing their explosive batting prowess.
title: 'Rohit is my No.1': Ex-player reveals his Top 5 T20I batters of 2024
Drones fall from sky at Florida Christmas event: Watch video

description: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau faces mounting pressure to resign amid dwindling support within the Liberal Party.  Following Deputy PM Chrystia Freeland's resignation, numerous MPs, including Chandra Arya and Anthony Housefather, have publicly called for Trudeau's departure.  With the NDP now willing to support efforts to topple the minority government, Trudeau's leadership is in serious jeopardy.
title: 'Time for PM to step aside': Canada's Trudeau faces internal revolt

description: Sunil Gavaskar criticises India's management for their treatment of Ravichandran Ashwin, highlighting his unjust exclusion from matches despite being a top-ranked bowler.  Gavaskar points out the double standard where struggling batsmen weren't dropped with the same frequency, and laments Ashwin's missed captaincy opportunities despite his significant contributions to Indian cricket.
title: Gavaskar criticises Indian team for neglecting Ashwin in overseas Tests

description: Pakistan made history by becoming the first team to sweep South Africa 3-0 in an ODI series in South Africa. Saim Ayub smashed his second century of the series; he scored 101 runs. Ayub joined the ranks of Virat Kohli, Joe Root, David Warner, Kevin Pietersen and Fakhar Zaman with his second ton of the series. Pakistan won the match by 36 runs (DLS method).
title: Pak batting star Saim Ayub joins Virat Kohli in this elite list

description: The Border-Gavaskar Trophy is level at 1-1 as India and Australia prepare for the crucial fourth Test at the MCG. Curator Matt Page promises a pitch similar to recent years, offering a balance between bat and ball with more grass to encourage seam movement. Spin is unlikely to be a significant factor.
title: MCG curator reveals what to expect from the pitch

description: Srinagar's Dal Lake froze over on Monday as a severe cold wave gripped Kashmir, forcing boat operators to break ice to navigate. Temperatures plummeted to -7°C, with the intense cold expected to continue.  Despite the frigid conditions, residents await snowfall. Kashmir's harsh winter period, 'Chillai Kalan,' will last until January 31, followed by 'Chillai-Khurd' and 'Chillai-Bachha'.
title: Kashmir reels under cold wave, Shikara operators struggle to navigate frozen lake

description: Indian-American entrepreneur Sriram Krishnan has been appointed as senior policy advisor for AI in the White House by US President-elect Donald Trump. Krishnan, close to Elon Musk, will focus on ensuring American leadership in AI and coordinate AI policy across government.
title: Indian-Americans celebrate Trump's appointment of Sriram Krishnan as AI advisor

description: A 2,000-year-old ossuary, possibly belonging to James, brother of Jesus, is on display in Atlanta. Inscribed "James, son of Joseph, brother of Jesus," its authenticity has been debated for years, though a judge deemed the inscription genuine. While acquitted of forgery charges, the ossuary's link to Jesus remains contested.
title: Box said to have 'Jesus’ brother’ bones' found in Israel, on display in US

description: GRAP, in all its four versions, is an emergency measure—a band-aid used when Delhi-NCR’s air quality turns poisonous. Like all emergency measures, it comes with inconveniences. But some of its measures are defeating the very purpose it’s used for.
title: Delhi-NCR air pollution: What GRAP shouldn’t do. And what it should

description: Jasprit Bumrah's exceptional performance with the ball has been crucial for India throughout the first three Tests on the tour of Australia. His guidance and advice have proven invaluable to the less experienced Indian pacers, who have struggled to match his consistency. Besides Bumrah's efforts, India's supporting bowlers need to step up to secure a victory in the Boxing Day Test at the MCG.
title: Will Bumrah's genius inspire his fellow pacers in Melbourne?

description: President-elect Trump has ignited a diplomatic firestorm by demanding Panama return control of the Panama Canal to the US. He alleges unfair pricing and criticizes the 1977 handover agreement. Panama's President Mulino vehemently rejected Trump's demand, defending Panama's sovereignty and the canal's fee structure. The canal, a key revenue source for Panama, recently faced drought-related disruptions and subsequent fee hikes.
title: 'Every sq. m of Panama Canal is ours': President Mulino reacts to Trump's threat

description: Twenty years ago, a young Mahendra Singh Dhoni began his international cricket journey with a run-out on his debut. He rose to become one of the greatest captains, leading India to victory in all three ICC trophies and achieving top Test rankings. Dhoni's IPL career with Chennai Super Kings saw him reach 10 finals, winning five.
title: 20 Years of MS Dhoni: Celebrating the legacy of a cricketing icon
'People have learned to take disorder as order': VP Dhankar's jibe at MPs

description: Three pro-Khalistan terrorists linked to a grenade attack on a Punjab police post were killed in a joint operation by Uttar Pradesh and Punjab police in Pilibhit.  Two AK-series assault rifles and two Glock pistols were recovered. The December 19th attack, claimed by Khalistan Zindabad Force, was the eighth such incident in Punjab since November 24th.
title: 3 pro-Khalistan terrorists killed in police encounter in UP's Pilibhit

description: Hockey captain Harmanpreet Singh, leading India to Olympic bronze, is nominated for the Major Dhyan Chand Khel Ratna award, alongside Paralympics gold medalist Praveen Kumar. Surprisingly, double-medal winning shooter Manu Bhaker's name is missing. Thirty athletes, including wrestler Aman Sehrawat and shooters Swapnil Kusale and Sarabjot Singh, are nominated for the Arjuna award.
title: Harmanpreet, Praveen for Khel Ratna; Manu's name missing

description: Sriram Krishnan, an Indian-American tech veteran, has been appointed as the White House's senior policy advisor on AI.  He will work alongside David Sacks to maintain US leadership in AI and shape national AI policy. Krishnan brings extensive experience from companies like Microsoft, Twitter, and Facebook, and recently departed Andreessen Horowitz.
title: Who is Sriram Krishnan? Indian-American chosen as Trump's AI policy advisor

description: KL Rahul, in top form, aims for a Boxing Day Test century hat-trick as India and Australia lock horns at the MCG for the pivotal third Test. With the series tied 1-1, Rahul's consistency against the new ball makes him a key player. The Boxing Day Test, set to begin on December 26.
title: KL Rahul chases 'unique hat-trick' in Boxing Day Test

description: An LPG tanker, en route from Gujarat to Uttar Pradesh, collided with a truck on the Jaipur-Ajmer highway after attempting a U-turn.  The resulting crash killed 13 people and injured over 30.  A special investigation team is probing the cause, focusing on the tanker's safety mechanisms and adherence to regulations for transporting hazardous materials. The tanker driver fled the scene.

description: Pakistan has chosen the UAE as the neutral venue for India's matches in the 2025 Champions Trophy, which will including the clash  Pakistan, likely on February 23rd.  This decision follows an agreement between the ICC, PCB, and BCCI to hold India-Pakistan matches in global events at neutral venues until 2027, resolving the deadlock after India's refusal to travel to Pakistan.
title: India vs Pakistan in Champions Trophy on Feb 23 in Dubai - Report

description: Hyderabad police arrested the parents of a minor girl for the murder of a 24-year-old man in 2023. The parents suspected the man had harmed their daughter after she ran away following an attempted assault. They lured him to a meeting, attacked him, and dumped his body in Nagarjunasagar.
title: Class 7 girl goes missing, parents trace online friend & murder him

description: WWE's Indian media rights are moving from Sony Pictures Networks India to Netflix India in a 10-year deal starting in 2025.  This marks Netflix India's first foray into sports entertainment, challenging rivals like Disney+ Hotstar and JioCinema.  The shift from traditional TV to streaming poses a challenge for attracting WWE's massive Indian fanbase to Netflix's platform.
title: Netflix India to take on Disney+ Hotstar, JioCinema's IPL 'shine' with ...

description: OpenAI CEO Sam Altman refuted investor Marc Andreessen's suggestion that the Biden administration intends to regulate AI to favor a select few companies. Altman denied any such discussions took place during meetings with government officials, dismissing the notion as a "conspiracy theory.
title: OpenAI CEO slams Marc Andreessen’s description of meetings with US govt

description: A 36-year-old woman from Dehradun was arrested in Jaipur for allegedly defrauding her newlywed husband, a jeweler, of valuables and cash worth over ₹36 lakh.  Police investigations revealed a history of similar scams spanning a decade, involving marriages, false accusations, and extortion targeting wealthy men across multiple cities.
title: ‘Luteri Dulhan’ who targeted wealthy men through matrimonial apps arrested

description: Lauren Sánchez celebrated her son Evan Whitesell's acceptance to the University of Miami.  Evan will be attending the same university as Kai Trump, granddaughter of President-elect Donald Trump.  Sánchez, who is engaged to Jeff Bezos, expressed pride in Evan's accomplishment, noting his perseverance despite dyslexia.
title: Trump's granddaughter Kai & Amazon founder Bezos' son to be collegemates

description: A 22-year-old woman, reported missing from Delhi on December 14th, was found deceased in a Paschim Vihar hotel room. Her boyfriend was later found dead near Gurgaon railway tracks. The couple was last seen together at a Punjabi Bagh restaurant on December 15th. While post-mortem shows no signs of physical assault on the woman, police await viscera reports.
title: Suicide pact or murder-suicide? Woman found dead in Delhi hotel
